## 4. FILE TYPE HANDLING

### 4a. Canonical Format Targets

| Detected Type | Output Format | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Video | `.mp4` (H.264, AAC audio) | All video normalizes to mp4 |
| Photo / Image | `.jpg` | Including RAW formats |
| Audio | `.mp3` | 192kbps |
| Unknown / Unsupported | Skip | Log the file as skipped |

### 4b. Input Formats to Handle

**Video:**
`.mp4`, `.mov`, `.mxf`, `.avi`, `.mkv`, `.wmv`, `.mts`, `.m2ts`, `.3gp`, `.flv`, `.webm`, `.ts`, `.vob`

**Photo:**
`.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.png`, `.bmp`, `.tiff`, `.tif`, `.webp`, `.heic`, `.heif`, `.arw`, `.cr2`, `.cr3`, `.nef`, `.orf`, `.raf`, `.dng`, `.rw2`

**Audio:**
`.mp3`, `.wav`, `.aac`, `.m4a`, `.flac`, `.ogg`, `.wma`, `.aiff`, `.opus`

**Ignored (log as skipped):**
`.pdf`, `.docx`, `.xlsx`, `.txt`, `.xml`, `.zip`, `.exe`, `.lnk`, and any unrecognized extension

### 4c. File Type Detection
- Use `python-magic` to detect true file type by reading file header bytes — do NOT rely on file extension alone. A `.mp4` renamed to `.mov` should still be handled correctly.

### 4d. Sorting Within Output
Inside each bucket (`clean`, `review`, `rejected`), files are separated into `/videos/`, `/photos/`, `/audio/` subfolders automatically based on their detected type.

